Here is a JavaScript function that sums all even numbers in an array:

```javascript
function sumEvenNumbers(arr) {
    let sum = 0;
    for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        if(arr[i] % 2 === 0) {
            sum += arr[i];
        }
    }
    return sum;
}
```

You can use this function by passing an array as an argument. For example:

```javascript
let arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6];
console.log(sumEvenNumbers(arr));  // Output: 12
```

In this example, the function will sum all the even numbers (2, 4, and 6) in the array and return the sum (12).

